radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled retrocecal appendix with a hyperemic and thickened wall and adjacent fat stranding. No free air or drainable fluid collection. Trace fluid tracks along the right pericolic gutter. Visualized lung fields within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum are within normal limits.
